# Update Engine (Phase 18)

Read **[UPDATE_ENGINE.md](../../UPDATE_ENGINE.md)** before any version deployment, maintenance window, migration, or rollout work.

## Core rule

**Updates only change Aipify software.** Never silently alter customer data, configuration, billing, domains, or permissions.

## Layer placement

| Concern | Layer | Paths |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Schedule rollout, audit, rollback | Platform | `app/platform/updates/`, `lib/update/` |
| Customer visibility (read-only) | Customer | `app/app/settings/updates/`, `components/app/update-engine/` |
| Version & update reporting | Embedded | `app/api/install/version`, `lib/embed/version.ts` |

## Rules

1. Classify every update: `patch` · `minor` · `major` · `security` · `database_migration`
2. Database migrations require explicit approval via `validateDatabaseMigration()` — no destructive auto-migrations
3. Notify customers before maintenance (Presence, bell, email, control center)
4. Log all events to `platform_update_audit_log`
5. Define rollback plan (`rollback_available`, `previous_version`, `rollback_steps`)
6. Customers cannot modify update logic — read-only in Settings → Updates
7. Embedded installs must validate token, domain, and tenant before reporting

> A safe update system is not optional. Customers must trust that Aipify improves without risking their data.
